name: df-pss
body: |- wb(wpss(c0, c1), wa(wss(c0, c1), wne(c0, c1)))
comment: Define proper subclass relationship between two classes. Definition 5.9 of [TakeutiZaring] p. 17. For example, ` { 1 , 2 } C. { 1 , 2 , 3 } ` ( ~ ex-pss ). Note that ` -. A C. A ` (proved in ~ pssirr ). Contrast this relationship with the relationship ` A C_ B ` (as defined in ~ df-ss ). Other possible definitions are given by ~ dfpss2 and ~ dfpss3 . (Contributed by NM, 7-Feb-1996.)
